Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.73,0:00:59.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些鱼是永远抓不到的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}There are some fish that cannot be caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.74,0:01:04.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这不是因为它们游的快或者比其他鱼强壮\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It's not that they're faster or stronger than other fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.24,0:01:07.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是他们有些与众不同\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}They're just touched by something extra.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.75,0:01:11.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这条鱼叫野兽\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}One such fish was The Beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.75,0:01:17.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我出生的那个时候他已经是个传奇人物了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And by the time I was born he was already a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.25,0:01:22.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他在阿拉巴马使鱼饵落空的次数比其他鱼多100次\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}He'd passed up more $ 100 lures than any fish in Alabama.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.26,0:01:26.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有人说这条鱼...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Some said that fish was the ghost of a thief...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.26,0:01:29.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是那个60年前在这条湖里淹死的小偷的亡灵\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...who'd drowned in that river 60 years before.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.77,0:01:35.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另外的人说他是白垩纪的恐龙\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Others claimed he was a dinosaur left over from the "Cruaceous" Period.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.77,0:01:39.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我对这种假设或者迷信不屑一顾\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I didn't put any stock into such speculation or superstition.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.78,0:01:42.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我曾经抓住过这条鱼...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}All I knew was I'd been trying to catch that fish...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.78,0:01:45.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...在我还没你大的时候\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...since I was a boy no bigger than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.78,0:01:48.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在你出生的那天....\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And on the day you were born...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.29,0:01:51.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是我抓住他的那天\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Well, that was the day I finally caught him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.79,0:01:55.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在  我要尝试所有的方法:\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, I'd tried everything on it:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.29,0:01:59.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虫子   诱饵   花生白脱   还有奶酪\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Worms, lures, peanut butter, peanut butter and cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.30,0:02:01.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是在那天我得到了个启示:\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}But on that day I had a revelation:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.80,0:02:04.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果那条鱼是亨利.华斯的灵魂\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}If that fish was Henry Walls' ghost, 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.21,0:02:06.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一般的诱饵是起不了作用的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}then the usual bait wasn't gonna work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.81,0:02:11.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我一定要用他最想得到的东西做诱饵\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I was gonna have to use something he truly desired.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.31,0:02:15.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你的手指? -黄金\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- Your finger? - Gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.31,0:02:18.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在   我把戒指系上了他们做的线...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, I tied my ring onto the strongest line they made...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.82,0:02:24.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...据他们说结实的在短短几分钟可以拉起一座桥\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...strong enough to hold up a bridge, they said, if only for a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.32,0:02:27.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我在上游投出了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And then I cast upriver.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.83,0:02:34.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那个怪物跳了起来  甚至还没等到接触水面就抓住了它\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The Beast jumped up and grabbed it before it even hit the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.83,0:02:39.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后非常迅速地折断了那条线\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And just as fast, he snapped clean through that line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.34,0:02:41.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你明白我的窘境了吧\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Well, you can see my predicament.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.34,0:02:45.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的结婚戒指   忠实於我妻子的标志...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}My wedding ring, the symbol of fidelity to my wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.34,0:02:48.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-...她马上要成为我孩子的妈妈了... -让他停下来\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...soon to be mother of my child... - Make him stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.35,0:02:51.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...现在已经在一条抓不到的鱼的肠子里了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...was now lost in the gut of an uncatchable fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.35,0:02:53.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你是怎么做的?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}What did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.35,0:02:57.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我从上游跟那个条鱼到下游\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I followed that fish upriver and downriver.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.36,0:03:00.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那条鱼   那个怪物...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}This fish, The Beast...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.86,0:03:06.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...我们一直称它为"他"   但是实际上应该是"她"\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...the whole time we were calling it a him, when in fact it was a her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.87,0:03:09.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它正怀着孩子  随时可能临产\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It was fat with eggs it was gonna lay any day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.37,0:03:12.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我就处在这种情况中\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, I was in a situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.37,0:03:16.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要割开那条鱼的肚子把我的结婚戒指取回来...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I could gut that fish and get my wedding ring back...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:18.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...但如果我这么做了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...but in doing so I'd 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.41,0:03:21.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就等於杀死了阿斯顿湖里最聪明的鱼\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}be killing the smartest catfish in the Ashton River.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.38,0:03:23.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要剥夺...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Did I want to deprive my son the chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.88,0:03:27.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...我的子孙抓住这条鱼的机会吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...to catch a fish like this of his own?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.89,0:03:29.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我和那条鱼夫人....\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}This ladyfish and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.89,0:03:34.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-我们有着相同的使命 -"我们都是相同等式的一部分"\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- Well, we had the same destiny. - "We were part of the same equation."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:37.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在  你也许会问...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, you may well ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.90,0:03:41.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦   亲爱的   亲爱的   这是你的夜晚\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh, darling, darling, it's still your night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.90,0:03:47.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...为什么对其他东西都无动於衷的它对金子下手那么快?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...why did it strike so quick on gold when nothing else would attract it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.91,0:03:50.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是从那天的事我学到的...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}That was the lesson I learned that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.91,0:03:54.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...我儿子出生的那天\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...the day my son was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.41,0:04:00.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时抓住一个女人的心的唯一方法...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Sometimes the only way to catch an uncatchable woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.42,0:04:04.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...就是给她一个结婚戒指\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...is to offer her a wedding ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:15.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么   父亲竟然不能和儿子说话?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}What, a father's not allowed to talk about his son?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.44,0:04:17.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个故事里我是个註解   爸爸...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I'm a footnote in that story, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.44,0:04:23.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...你这个奇遇从来就没有发生过\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...the context for your great adventure, which never happened, incidentally.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.44,0:04:26.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我出生的时候你在威齐塔卖气货\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You were selling novelty products in Wichita when I was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.95,0:04:29.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来吧   威尔. 每个人都喜欢这个故事!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Come on, Will. Everyone loves that story!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:33.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是的. 我就不喜欢.已经听了几千遍了!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}They don't. I don't love that story. Not anymore. Not after a thousand times!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.96,0:04:38.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道每个要点   父亲 我能像那样再说一遍了!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I know every punch line, Dad. I can tell them as well as you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.96,0:04:41.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个晚上   我生命中的一个晚上...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}For one night, one night in your entire life...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.96,0:04:44.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...宇宙不再绕着爱德华.布鲁旋转\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...the universe did not revolve around Edward Bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.97,0:04:49.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你为什么不能理解呢? -很抱歉麻烦你了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- How can you not understand that? - I'm sorry to embarrass you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.47,0:04:53.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在烦你自己   爸爸. 只是你自己不知道\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You're embarrassing yourself, Dad. You just don't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.48,0:04:59.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那晚以后  我三年没有再和我父亲说过话\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}After that night, I didn't speak to my father again for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.99,0:05:09.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,威廉.布鲁   联合国际报. 如果我能--\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}William Bloom, United Press International. If I could just...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:15.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想我们可以间接地沟通\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}We communicated indirectly, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.50,0:05:19.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在她的信和圣诞卡里   我妈妈写信给她们两个\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}In her letters and Christmas cards, my mother wrote for both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.00,0:05:21.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我打电话去的时候  \N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And when I'd call, 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.51,0:05:25.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她总是说父亲驾车出去了 或者是在游泳池里游泳\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}she'd say Dad was out driving or swimming in the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.01,0:05:28.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就这样   我们再也没有说话\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}True to form, we never talked about not talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.01,0:05:35.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上   我没有在我父亲身上看到我\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The truth is, I didn't see anything of myself in my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.02,0:05:38.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我相信他也没在我身上找到他的影子\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And I don't think he saw anything of himself in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:46.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们就像相互瞭解的陌生人\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}We were like strangers who knew each other very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.53,0:05:53.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,说起我父亲这一生的故事...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}In telling the story of my father's life...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.04,0:05:55.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...很难把事实和虚幻分开  \N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...it's impossible to separate fact from fiction, 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.63,0:05:58.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他是一个有着传奇色彩的人物\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}the man from the myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:04.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最好的办法是我把他告诉我的複述出来\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The best I can do is to tell it the way he told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:10.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,故事不一定合理   可能大多数没有发生过\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It doesn't always make sense, and most of it never happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:37.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把我的戒指还给我!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Give me back my ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.09,0:06:51.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.59,0:06:55.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这种故事就是这样的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}But that's what kind of story this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.61,0:07:07.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他的出生便为他以后的生活打下了基础\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}His birth would set the pace for his unlikely life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.11,0:07:10.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有比大多数人活的长   但是伟大\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}No longer than most men's, but larger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.11,0:07:12.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他的故事越离奇...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And as strange as his stories got...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.62,0:07:16.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,... 故事的结局就越出人意料\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...the endings were always the most surprising of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.15,0:07:46.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对. 对   他在这\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Yes. Yes, he's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.65,0:07:48.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是你母亲\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It's your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.66,0:07:58.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,本耐特医生怎么说?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And what does Dr. Bennett say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.66,0:08:02.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不  当然  我要他听电话\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}No, sure, I'll talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.67,0:08:05.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好  我等\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Yeah, I'll wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.17,0:08:06.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,情况不好?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It's bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.67,0:08:11.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对   比他们想像的还糟 他们要停止化疗\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Yeah, it's more than they thought. They're gonna stop chemo.
