Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.72,0:17:14.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说我的   你写你的. 一回事\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I speak mine out, you write yours down. Same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.73,0:17:17.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爸爸....\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.23,0:17:23.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想在我在这的时候谈些事\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I hope to talk about some things while I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.74,0:17:25.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的意思是我在这\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You mean while I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.74,0:17:29.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我只是想知道事情的真相:\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I just want to know the true versions of things:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.75,0:17:32.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真实的事和编造的故事\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Events. Stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.75,0:17:34.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.76,0:17:48.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你妈妈没有保住游泳池\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Your mother hasn't been keeping up the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.26,0:17:52.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-如果你想做  你可以修一下 -恩   我会的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- lf you wanted to, you could fix it. - Yeah, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.27,0:17:55.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你知道化学药品在哪吗? -你出门的时候我做的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- You know where the chemicals are? - I did it when you were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.77,0:18:02.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我从来不喜欢在家呆着   威尔. 太拘束了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I was never much for being at home, Will. Too confining.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.28,0:18:05.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而现在   却被困在床上....\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And this here, being stuck in bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.28,0:18:09.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等死是我一生中最糟糕的事\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Dying is the worst thing that's ever happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.79,0:18:15.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-我想你说的是你不会死 -我说的不是我是怎么死的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- I thought you said you weren't dying. - I said this isn't how I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.29,0:18:19.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后部分最不寻常\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The last part is much more unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.80,0:18:22.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相信我的话\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Trust me on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.83,0:18:57.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,本耐特大夫说我要在家呆一星期\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Dr. Bennett said I have to stay at home for a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.84,0:19:01.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦   没什么. 有一次   我在床上呆了3年\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh, that's nothing. Once, I had to stay in bed for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.84,0:19:05.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-是你得水痘的那次? -是就好了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- Did you have the chickenpox? - I wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.36,0:19:27.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上   没人知道那里出错了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Truth is, no one quite knew what was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.36,0:19:30.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个人成长的大多数时间...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Most times a person grows up gradually...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.37,0:19:33.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...当我瞭解我自己的时候\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...while I found myself in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.87,0:19:40.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的肌肉  我的骨骼   无法跟上我的身体猛长的速度\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}My muscles and my bones couldn't keep up with my body's ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.38,0:19:43.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我在床上渡过了三年大好时光...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}So I spent the better part of three years confined to my bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.88,0:19:47.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,... 看百科全书是我唯一的探索方式\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...with the encyclopedia being my only means of exploration.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.89,0:19:50.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我看到了G部...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I had made it all the way to the G's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.39,0:19:53.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...想要找到"巨人症"的答案...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...hoping to find an answer to my "gigantificationism"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.89,0:19:57.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,... 当我翻开一篇关於金鱼的文章的时候\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...when I uncovered an article about the common goldfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.40,0:20:01.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"放在一个小碗里   金鱼会变小\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}"Kept in a small bowl, the goldfish will remain small.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.40,0:20:02.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地方大了...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}With more space...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.90,0:20:06.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...金鱼就会两倍三倍的长大"\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...the fish will grow double, triple, or quadruple its size."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.90,0:20:10.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我似乎找到了我狂长的原因...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It occurred to me then that perhaps the reason for my growth...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.41,0:20:12.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...是因为我要做大事\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...was that I was intended for larger things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.91,0:20:16.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,毕竟   伟大的人身躯都很魁梧\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}After all, a giant man can't have an ordinary-sized life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.92,0:20:21.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到我的骨骼发育成型...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}As soon as my bones had settled in their adult configuration...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.42,0:20:26.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...我就开始计划在阿斯顿打开更广阔的天地\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...I set upon my plan to make a bigger place for myself in Ashton.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.42,0:20:28.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,老虎   走!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Tigers, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.44,0:20:45.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爱德华.布鲁!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Edward Bloom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.99,0:21:32.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小狗! 我的小狗! 我的小狗被困住了!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Doggy! My doggy! My doggy's trapped!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.00,0:21:44.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是我在阿斯顿看到最大的事件\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I was the biggest thing Ashton had ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.01,0:21:48.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到一天   一个陌生人来到这\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Until one day, a stranger arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.02,0:22:08.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冷静. 冷静   大家冷静. 已经够了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Calm down. Calm down, everybody. Calm down. That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.03,0:22:12.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-市长先生   他把玉米地吃遍了 -他吃了我的狗\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- Mr. Mayor, he ate an entire corn field. - He ate my dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.03,0:22:14.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果市长你不去阻止他的话  我们去\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}If you ain't gonna stop him, mayor, we will.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.54,0:22:18.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不允许镇上存在暴力\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I won't have mob violence in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.04,0:22:20.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有没有人和他谈谈?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, has someone tried talking to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.04,0:22:23.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你不能和他讲道理 -他是个恶人\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- You can't reason with him. - He's a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.04,0:22:25.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我去吧\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.06,0:22:41.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我和他谈谈. 看看能不能让他走\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I'll talk to him. See if I can get him to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.56,0:22:44.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那傢伙会把你压扁的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}That creature could crush you without trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.57,0:22:48.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦   相信我   他会走的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh, trust me, he'll have to try.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.60,0:23:20.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喂?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.11,0:23:28.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我叫爱德华.布鲁   我要和你谈谈!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}My name is Edward Bloom, and I wanna talk to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.61,0:23:31.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,滚!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.12,0:23:36.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不现身我哪都不去!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, I'm not going anywhere until you show yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.12,0:23:39.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说   滚啊!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I said, go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.64,0:24:02.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我已经预知自己是怎么死的...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Armed with the foreknowledge of my own death...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.15,0:24:04.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...所以我知道那巨人杀不了我\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...I knew the giant couldn't kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.65,0:24:10.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过   希望不要把我的骨头拧断\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}All the same, I preferred to keep my bones unbroken.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.15,0:24:12.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么在这?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.16,0:24:15.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以吃我了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}So you can eat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.66,0:24:19.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个镇决定献上个人祭  那人就是我\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The town decided to send a human sacrifice and I volunteered.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.16,0:24:23.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的手臂筋比较多   不过我大腿上的肉还是蛮好吃的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}My arms are a little stringy, but there's some good eating in my legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.17,0:24:27.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的意思是   我自己都想吃\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I mean, I'd be tempted to eat them myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.67,0:24:31.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我猜....\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}So I guess, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.18,0:24:35.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你动作快点的话我就不会疼   真的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}If you'd just get it over with quick, because I'm not much for pain, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.69,0:24:51.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦   来吧! 我不能回去了! 我是个人祭!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh, come on! I can't go back! I'm a human sacrifice!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.20,0:24:54.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我回去了   他们一定认为我是懦夫\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}If I go back, they'll think I'm a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.20,0:24:57.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我情愿做晚餐也不做懦夫\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I'd rather be dinner than a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.70,0:24:59.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.20,0:25:02.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以从我的手开始. 那很开胃\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You can start with my hand. It'll be an appetizer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.71,0:25:06.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不想吃你 我不想吃任何人\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I don't want to eat you. I don't want to eat anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.71,0:25:11.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我只是太饿了. 我太高了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I just get so hungry. I'm just too big.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.22,0:25:15.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想过你其实并不高吗...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Did you ever think that maybe you're not too big...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.22,0:25:17.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...也许是镇上的人太矮了呢?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...but maybe this town is just too small?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.22,0:25:20.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我听说有些城市的建筑很高...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I've heard in real cities there are buildings so tall...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.22,0:25:22.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...你还看不到他们的顶部\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...you can't even see the tops of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.73,0:25:25.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-真的? -哦   我不会骗你的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- Really? - Oh, I wouldn't lie to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.23,0:25:27.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是可随便享用的自助餐\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And all-you-can-eat buffets.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.73,0:25:30.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你可以吃很多   对吗? -是的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- Now, you can eat a lot, can't you? - I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.73,0:25:34.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那你为什么在这个小镇上浪费时间?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}So why are you wasting your time in a small town?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.24,0:25:37.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你是个巨人. 你应该去大城市\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You're a big man. You should be in a big city.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.24,0:25:40.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你是要让我走   对吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You're just trying to get me to leave, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.75,0:25:44.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你叫什么   巨人? -卡尔.\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- What's your name, giant? - Karl.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.25,0:25:48.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我叫爱德华. 说实话....\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Well, mine's Edward. And truthfully...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.25,0:25:52.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是想让你走   卡尔. 但是是和你一起走\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Well, I do want you to leave, Karl. But I want to leave with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.26,0:25:55.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的意思是   你觉得这个镇对你来说太小了吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I mean, you think this town is too small for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.26,0:25:58.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对我的雄心来说也太小了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Well, it's too small for a man of my ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.26,0:26:01.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么说? 要不要和我一起走?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}So, what do you say? Join me?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.77,0:26:06.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.27,0:26:08.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.77,0:26:12.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先   我们要为去的城市做好准备\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, first, we gotta get you ready for the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.80,0:26:33.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爱德华.布鲁   阿斯顿的长子...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Edward Bloom, first son of Ashton...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.30,0:26:37.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...怀着沉重的心情为你送行\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...it's with a heavy heart that we see you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.30,0:26:39.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,请带上城市钥匙...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}But take with you this key to the city...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.81,0:26:42.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...你随时都能回来...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...and know that any time you want to come back...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.81,0:26:46.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...我们的大门为你敞开\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...all our doors are open to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.82,0:26:58.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我离开阿斯顿的那个下午   似乎所有人都有忠告\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}That afternoon as I left Ashton, everyone seemed to have advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.82,0:27:02.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给你自己找个好姑娘  要快!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Find yourself a nice girl, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.33,0:27:05.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,别失去自尊   爱德华.布鲁!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Watch your pride, Edward Bloom!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.33,0:27:10.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是有个人的忠告我最重视\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}But there was one person whose counsel I held above all others.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.84,0:27:16.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他说湖里的那条大鱼...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}She said that the biggest fish in the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.34,0:27:20.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...从来没有被抓过\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...gets that way by never being caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.35,0:27:28.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-她说了什么? -打我\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- What'd she say? - Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.37,0:27:41.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离开阿斯顿有两条路:\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}There were two roads out of Ashton:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.37,0:27:44.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新的已经铺好了路面 旧的没有\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}A new one which was paved and an older one that wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.87,0:27:46.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大家都不走旧的那条...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}People didn't use the old one anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.87,0:27:49.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...传说那里闹鬼\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...and it had developed a reputation for being haunted.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.88,0:27:53.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我不想再回阿斯顿了...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Well, since I had no intention of ever returning to Ashton...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.38,0:27:57.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,... 看来这次是个好机会看看老路有什么\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...this seemed as good a time as any to find out what lay down that old one.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.89,0:28:02.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你知道谁走过吗? -那个诗人   诺什.温丝勒走过\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- You know anyone who's taken it? - That poet, Norther Winslow, did.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.89,0:28:05.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他去了法国巴黎\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}He was going to Paris, France.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.39,0:28:09.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我猜他喜欢那里. 没人再有他的消息了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I guess he liked it. No one ever heard from him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.40,0:28:11.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要告诉你. 你选另外条路\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I'll tell you what. You go the other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.40,0:28:15.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在这抄小路   在那头见\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I'll cut through here, and I'll meet you on the far side.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.40,0:28:19.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你是想逃走  对吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You're just trying to run away, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.91,0:28:22.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拿着\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.41,0:28:27.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了让你相信  你可以拿着我的包\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Just to be sure, you can take my pack.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.95,0:29:08.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么   你这个狗娘--\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Why, you son of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.48,0:29:36.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是说一个有理智的人...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, there comes a point when a reasonable man...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.49,0:29:41.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...在这时候会放下尊严  承认自己犯了个天大的错误\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...will swallow his pride and admit that he's made a terrible mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.49,0:29:46.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实是  我从来就不是个有理智的人\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The truth is, I was never a reasonable man.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.50,0:29:50.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想起了才主日学校的事...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And what I recall of Sunday school was that...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.50,0:29:56.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...事情越艰难   到最后得到的回报越大\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...the more difficult something is, the more rewarding it is in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.70,0:30:57.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,朋友! 欢迎你!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Friend! Welcome to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.20,0:31:01.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你叫什么? -爱德华.布鲁.\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- What's your name? - Edward Bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.21,0:31:05.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-就像花那样"盛开" ? -对的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- "Bloom" like a flower? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.21,0:31:09.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦   这里! 你来啦  来这了 "爱德华.布鲁."\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh, here! Here you are, right here. "Edward Bloom."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.71,0:31:12.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还没想到你会来\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}We weren't expecting you yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.22,0:31:14.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你们想我? -还没\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- You were expecting me? - Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.72,0:31:16.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你一定没有走捷径. \N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You must've taken a shortcut. 
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.55,0:31:19.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么   我走了. 差点杀了我自己\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Why, yes, I did. It almost killed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.72,0:31:24.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人生会给你这些教训. 事实上   长的路往往比较好走\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Life will do that to you. And truthfully, the long way is easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.23,0:31:27.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-但是这也太长了. -长的多\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- But it's longer. - Much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.23,0:31:30.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在你在这 这才是关键\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And you're here now, and that's what matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.23,0:31:31.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是哪?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.74,0:31:35.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幽灵镇. 阿拉巴马最好的藏身之处!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The town of Spectre. Best-kept secret in Alabama!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.24,0:31:38.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里说你是来自阿斯顿的  对吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, it says here you're from Ashton, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.74,0:31:42.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在阿斯顿遇见的最后一个人是诺什.温丝勒.\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Last person we had from Ashton was Norther Winslow.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.25,0:31:44.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那个诗人? 他怎么了?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The poet? Whatever happened to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.25,0:31:49.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他仍然在这. 我给你弄点喝的. 我把所有事都告诉你\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}He's still here. Let me buy you a drink. I'll tell you all about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.25,0:31:50.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该死   我让他告诉你!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Hell, I'll have him tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.26,0:31:54.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要见些人   已经迟到了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I have to meet somebody, and I'm already running late.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.26,0:31:58.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,孩子   我告诉你. 你来早了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, son, I already told you. You're early.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.80,0:32:36.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我这是不是你吃过的最好吃的馅饼\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, tell me if that isn't the best pie you ever ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.80,0:32:38.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,确实是\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It truly is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.31,0:32:47.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里什么都好. 水也很清甜\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Well, everything tastes better here. Even the water is sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.31,0:32:52.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是太热  太冷   太潮湿\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Never gets too hot, too cold, too humid.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.32,0:32:55.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在晚上   清风拂过树林...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}At night, the wind goes through the trees where you'd swear...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.82,0:33:00.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...你就感觉是大型交响乐团为你演奏\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...there was a whole symphony out there playing just for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.33,0:33:04.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿! 珍妮!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Hey! Jenny!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.33,0:33:07.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,回来这里!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Come back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.34,0:33:14.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,珍妮!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Jenny!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.36,0:33:31.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿   我要那些\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Hey, I need those.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.86,0:33:35.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-没有比这镇上更松软的土地了 -就像首诗\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- There is no softer ground than town. - That almost rhymes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.36,0:33:38.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他是我们这最傑出的诗人. 来吧\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}He's our poet laureate. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.37,0:33:45.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我答应在这过个下午   只是想知道...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I agreed to spend the afternoon, if only to understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.37,0:33:50.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...为什么这里感觉这么陌生\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...the mystery of how a place could feel so strange and yet so familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.88,0:33:56.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这首诗我已经写了12年\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I've been working on this poem for 12 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.38,0:33:58.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.38,0:34:03.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人们都很期望. 我不想辜负他们\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}There's a lot of expectation. I don't wanna disappoint my fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.89,0:34:05.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我可以吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}May I?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.91,0:34:28.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有三行\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It's only three lines long.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.92,0:34:34.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是你不要把未成品给人看的原因\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}This is why you should never show a work in progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.98,0:35:32.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我抓住了!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I got him!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.50,0:35:49.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,里面有水蛭\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}There's leeches in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.00,0:35:53.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你看见那个女人了吗? -她看起来怎么样?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- Did you see that woman? - What did she look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.50,0:35:57.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-她是.... -裸体的?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- Well, she was... - Was she naked?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.01,0:36:00.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Yes, she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.51,0:36:05.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是女人.是鱼. 没有人抓住过她\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It's not a woman. It's a fish. No one ever catches her.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.51,0:36:08.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每个人看到的鱼都不一样\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Fish looks different to different people.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.02,0:36:12.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我爸爸说它们看上去就像他小时候养的猎犬...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}My daddy said it looked like the coon dog he had when he was a kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.52,0:36:15.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...起死回生\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...back from the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.03,0:36:20.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦   该死\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh, darn.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.03,0:36:24.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你几岁了? -18\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- How old are you? - Eighteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.53,0:36:28.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我8岁. 那就是说在我18岁的时候   你就28了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I'm 8. That means when I'm 18, you'll be 28.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.54,0:36:33.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-而我28岁的时候  你也才38. -你的数学不错\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- And when I'm 28, you'll only be 38. - You're pretty good at arithmetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.54,0:36:38.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我38岁的时候   你48. 没多大区别\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And when I'm 38, you'll be 48. That's not much difference at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.05,0:36:41.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有很大区别   尽管   不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Sure is a lot now, though, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.58,0:37:17.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿   爱德华!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Hey, Edward!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.58,0:37:27.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,玫瑰是红的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.28,0:37:30.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,紫罗兰是蓝的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.60,0:37:33.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我爱幽灵镇....\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I love Spectre...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.61,0:37:41.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对不起\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.62,0:37:50.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,珍妮 觉得你人不错 我们都这样认为\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Jenny thinks you're quite a catch. We all do.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.12,0:37:52.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.62,0:37:56.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说   你人不错\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I said, you're quite a catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.15,0:38:20.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要走了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I have to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.66,0:38:25.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今晚\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.66,0:38:27.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.16,0:38:31.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对这个镇我不能要求更多了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}This town is more than any man could ask for.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.16,0:38:34.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我要在这停下来   我会觉得我的运气不错\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And if I were to end up here, I would consider myself lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.67,0:38:39.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但实际上是   我还没准备好在哪停下来\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}But the truth is, I'm just not ready to end up anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.17,0:38:41.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是没人离开过这\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}But no one's ever left.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.18,0:38:45.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没鞋你怎么走?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}How are you gonna make it without your shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.68,0:38:48.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想会疼. 很疼\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Well, I suspect it will hurt. A lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.18,0:38:55.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对不起   但是.... 再见\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Now, I'm sorry, but... Well, goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.69,0:39:02.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你不会找到更好的地方的. -我也不想\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- You won't find a better place. - I don't expect to.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.70,0:39:09.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,答应我不要回来\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Promise me you'll come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.70,0:39:16.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的. 将来. 当我真的要回来的时候\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I promise. Someday. When I'm really supposed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.74,0:39:50.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那晚   我有两个结论\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}That night, I reached two conclusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.24,0:39:55.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第一个是险路在黑暗中会变得更险\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The first was that a dangerous path is made much worse by darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.25,0:40:00.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第二个是我绝望而不不可避免地迷了路\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The second was that I was hopelessly and irrevocably lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.75,0:40:04.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些树林成了我的葬身之处\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}These woods would become my graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.76,0:40:08.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然去往幽灵镇的路困难重重 \N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}As difficult as it was to reach Spectre, 
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.46,0:40:11.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我还是注定最终到达了那里\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I was fated to get there eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.27,0:40:15.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,毕竟  没有人可以逃避走到人生的尽头\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}After all, no man can avoid reaching the end of his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.28,0:40:33.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这时我认识到  这不是我的人生的尽头\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}And then I realized this wasn't the end of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.79,0:40:37.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不是这么死的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}This isn't how I die.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.81,0:40:55.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,朋友\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.81,0:41:00.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你的鞋怎么了? -他们走在我的前头了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- What happened to your shoes? - They kind of got ahead of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.33,0:41:19.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道你看见了没   但是傑瑟芬有照片...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I don't know if you saw it, but Josephine had some photos...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.83,0:41:21.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...就在最近的新闻周刊上\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...in the most recent Newsweek.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.84,0:41:25.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.34,0:41:27.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太棒了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}That's just wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.35,0:41:33.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我花了一周时间在摩洛哥拍那篇报道. 太不可思议了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I spent a week in Morocco for the story. It was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.35,0:41:38.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦.我们要出个拷贝\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh. We'll have to pick up a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.86,0:41:51.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道你有没有意识到   傑瑟芬...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I don't know if you're aware of this, Josephine...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.37,0:41:54.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...但是非洲鹦鹉  \N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...but African parrots,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.22,0:41:57.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在它们的老家刚果   他们只会说法语\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&} in their native Congo, they speak only French.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.87,0:41:59.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.88,0:42:03.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能让他们说几句英语你就很走运了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You're lucky to get four words out of them in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.38,0:42:06.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是如果你穿过森林...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}But if you were to walk through the jungle...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.38,0:42:10.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...你会听到它们说最棒的法语\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...you'd hear them speaking the most elaborate French.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.89,0:42:15.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些鹦鹉什么都谈. 政治  电影  时装\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Those parrots talk about everything. Politics, movies, fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.89,0:42:19.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,任何事情  除了宗教\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Everything but religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.90,0:42:21.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么不说宗教   爸爸?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Why not religion, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.90,0:42:26.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,说宗教太粗鲁了. 你不会知道你会冒犯什么的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It's rude to talk about religion. You never know who you're gonna offend.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.91,0:42:35.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,傑瑟芬实际上去年去了刚果\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Josephine actually went to the Congo last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.91,0:42:39.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦   所以你知道\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh, so you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.43,0:42:56.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你好\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.93,0:42:59.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗨.你怎么样?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Hi. How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.44,0:43:04.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦   我在作梦\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh, I was dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.44,0:43:07.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,梦见什么了?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}What were you dreaming about?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.94,0:43:10.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦   我通常不太记得...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh, I don't usually remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.95,0:43:15.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...除非很有预兆. 你知道这些梦是什么意思吗?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...unless they're especially portentous. Do you know what that word means?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.95,0:43:19.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,意思就是你梦见了可能发生的事\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}It means when you dream about something that's gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.46,0:43:21.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像那晚   我做了个梦...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Like one night, I had a dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.96,0:43:26.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...一只乌鸦飞过来说:\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...where this crow came and said:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.96,0:43:30.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"你的阿姨会死"\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}"Your aunt is gonna die."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.97,0:43:33.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我很惊慌   叫醒了父母...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I was so scared, I woke up my parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.97,0:43:38.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...但是他们说只是个梦就又都睡了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...but they said it was just a dream and to get back to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.48,0:43:42.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是隔天早上   我的史坦斯阿姨就死了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}But the next morning, my Aunt Stacy was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.48,0:43:44.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太可怕了\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}That's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.48,0:43:46.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对她来说太可怕了 \N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Terrible for her,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.41,0:43:50.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是想想我   一个孩子有这种力量\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&} but think about me, young boy with that kind of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.49,0:43:54.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不到三周  那只乌鸦又到了我的梦中...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Wasn't three weeks later when the crow came back to me in a dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.99,0:44:00.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...说   "你爸爸会死"\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...and said, "Your daddy's gonna die."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.50,0:44:03.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道该怎么办\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I didn't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.00,0:44:07.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后我告诉了我父亲   但他说:\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I finally told my father, but he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.01,0:44:13.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"哦   不要担心." 但是我看的出他很慌张\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}"Oh, not to worry." But I could see he was rattled.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.01,0:44:16.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第二天   他变了个人\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}The next morning, he wasn't himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.01,0:44:20.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到处看   像是在等什么东西砸他脑袋\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Kept looking around, waiting for something to drop on his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.02,0:44:26.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为乌鸦没说会怎么样   只是说:\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Because the crow didn't say how it was gonna happen, just those words:
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.02,0:44:28.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"你爸爸会死"\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}"Your daddy's gonna die."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.03,0:44:35.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他很早出去  去了很久\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Well, he left home early and was gone a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.03,0:44:38.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当他回来的时候   他看上去脸色很吓人...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}When he finally came back, he looked terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.04,0:44:41.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...就像等了一天斧子掉下来\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...like he was waiting for the ax to fall all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.04,0:44:44.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他跟妈妈说:\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}He said to my mother:
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.04,0:44:48.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"这是我一生中最糟的一天"\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}"I've just had the worst day of my life."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.05,0:44:52.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"你觉得这是你一生中最糟的一天?" 她说\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}"You think you've had a bad day?" she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.05,0:44:57.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"这个早上   送牛奶的在台阶上死了"\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}"This morning, the milkman dropped dead on the porch."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.56,0:45:04.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我母亲和他偷情\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Because, see, my mother was banging the milkman.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.57,0:45:10.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-我能给你拍张照吗? -哦   你不需要照片\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- Can I take your picture? - Oh, you don't need a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.07,0:45:14.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,查一下 "英俊"这个词\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Just look up the word "handsome" in the dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.57,0:45:16.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,请?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Please?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.58,0:45:19.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.58,0:45:25.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在婚礼的照片上看到你\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I have photos of the wedding to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.09,0:45:27.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你和我父亲在一起很不错\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}There is a great one of you and my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.59,0:45:38.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想看看你婚礼的照片 我没看过\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I want to see pictures of your wedding. I've never seen any.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.10,0:45:42.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们没举办过真正的婚礼\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}That's because we didn't have a proper wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.10,0:45:45.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的婆婆本不应嫁给我\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Your mother-in-law was never supposed to marry me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.61,0:45:49.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-她已经和别人订了婚. -我不知道\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}- She was engaged to somebody else. - I never knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.61,0:45:52.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,威尔没有告诉你?\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Will never told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.61,0:45:55.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能这样也好\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Probably just as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.11,0:45:58.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,说不定他会讲错话\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}He would have told it wrong, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.12,0:46:01.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上   没有一点添油加醋\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}All the facts, none of the flavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.62,0:46:05.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦. 这就是那个传说\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Oh. So this is a tall tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.13,0:46:09.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,故事并不短\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Well, it's not a short one.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.13,0:46:14.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我刚刚离开幽灵镇去寻找我的使命\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}I'd just left Spectre and was on my way to discover my destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.14,0:46:20.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不太清楚那是什么...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Not knowing what that would be exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.14,0:46:25.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...我寻找每个机会\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...I explored every opportunity that presented itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.18,0:46:58.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可可! 可可! 他们在那\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Coco! Coco! There they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.18,0:47:02.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,女士们先生们!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Ladies and gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.18,0:47:07.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你也许会想你看见了什么非同寻常的东西\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You may think you've seen the unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.69,0:47:12.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你也许认为自己看到了荒诞的东西\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}You may think you've seen the bizarre.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.19,0:47:18.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是我找遍了世界的任何角落...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}But I've traveled to the five corners of the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.20,0:47:25.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...让你知道   我从没有看见过这种东西!\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...and let me tell you, I've never seen anything like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.21,0:47:32.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我遇见那个男人的时候...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}When I met this man...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.72,0:47:35.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...他正在弗罗里达州摘桔子\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}...he was picking oranges in Florida.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.22,0:47:39.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他的同事叫他佩努. "影子"\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}His fellow workers called him El Penumbra. "The Shadow."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.22,0:47:44.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为当你在他旁边干活时...\N{\fnTahoma}{\fs14}{\c&H00FFFF&}{\3c&H000000&}Because when you worked beside him...
